caption: Food was ok won't be coming back they don't serve ice with there water  and the mens restroom wasn't cleaned very well we arrived at 4:05 when they had just opened so no excuse for that my friend ordered his burger well done it came out medium the food presentation is wonderful in there photos but taste wise it's ok nothing to brag about

Saw them on Chicago's Best on WGN TV and they are EVERYTHING you saw on the episode!! We took our son for his 21st birthday, and he already wants to bring his girlfriend back! We shared the super crispy spicy wings, sweet wings, fondue pork frittes, and popcorn chicken, mom had the Ganbeii salad and he had the Nomad burger. All of the food was AMAZING, the plum soju was great, and even though none of us like beer, we discovered that we actually kinda like the Korean mango beer and may play around with those some more. The music playing was a really cool mix, and Zuke (the manager) was very attentive, observed covid-19 protocols, and made the trip PERFECT!!! We will definitely be back to enjoy the patio as the weather gets better.

We’ve been twice in the past week and a half. Amazing fusion!!! Cannot wait to eat there in person once we’re vaccinated. These folks are also the nicest. HIGHLY RECOMMEND - a person who has never written a review

I went to Ganbeii with a group of friends to eat and drink and had an amazing time!!! We wanted to watch the bulls game so the staff put it on for us right away! But most importantly the wings and ribs were up there with the best I’ve ever had!!! The staff was so kind and served us drinks until they closed and by that time I had to order more ribs to go!!! If you are looking for great Asian BBQ Ganbeii is the place to go. They also have an amazing burger that’s more of an Asian/American take.  Delicious food Great drinks Great staff Can’t go wrong !!!!!!

I decided to visit this place after hearing about it from my a lot of people in the area. I had been interested in this place after hearing about their Mongolian dishes(I've been to Mongolia several times and loved it). It is a warm, comfortable place with a relaxing atmosphere for a good time. The servers are consistent and kind, with a lot of attention payed to detail. The food was delicious. It reminded me of my time overseas. I recommend the Mongolian BBQ. The servings are plentiful, and for the price you can't beat It. The "icing on the cake" is the imported beer from Asia. 10/10 I'm defiantly coming back.
The food here was amazing! The wings and the fries were our favorite! Service was excellent! Will be back
The ribs are amazing 👏

We ordered delivery through Grubhub, and in short, we won't order from here again. Food arrived 30 min late and was luke-warm / cool. The burger was 4 stars, almost definitely would have been 5 if warm. The fries were cold and inedible. Bao and rice bowl were good, but room temperature, so definitely not great. We were so excited to try Urban Nomads after our alderman talked it up, but this was a disappointing experience.
Good food and cozy atmosphere.

Stopped by for the first time and we ordered the burger and the wings. The burger was good, hearty size plus fries on the side, but the wings were the real standout. Perfectly spicy and crunchy, plus a great portion size and very meaty. Would definitely order again!
Had their burger and that was awesome, bomb one of the best burgers I’ve ever had definitely going back soon three thumbs up

Very delicious and unique taste between Asian and American food. Satisfied 100% plus delivery was very quick and dinner was hot. Happy to support local businesses that are working hard to bring us quality food. Thank you.

The food here is great! I have to eat gluten free and they are so knowledgeable! It’s great to have the level of reassurance they offer. They chicken and rice are both gluten free and great every time! I can’t recommend this place enough!

Great food, friendly service, convenient ordering process for to-go orders. They just added ramen to the menu and it’s fantastic! Perfect for this time of year.
One of the best restaurant around! Food was amazing and great quality! Service was astounding! I will definitely be coming back!

Ordered a sandwich and fries for takeout - WOW. Food was incredible, it was ready fast, and fairly priced. I can't wait to get it again.

Fantastic burgers. Fantastic fries. Excellent service. We stopped in for lunch on a Friday and were seated immediately. I believe this is also great place for hang out with friends and family with having great burgers and drinks.  I love Urban Nomad Burger.
Slowly finishing up everything on their menu.. this time I had their “Urban Nomad Burger” very hearty, juicy, perfectly cooked. Coming back to try their ribs next week!

Me and my girl both really enjoyed this Asian American BBQ place. Uno (one of the guys behind the counter) took great care of us and made sure everything was above and beyond. I had the Brisket, which was mouth watering good. Best I have had in the area. The bbq sauce is on the side, like all good BBQ places should be, and is a nice balance between sweet and spicy that is very smooth on the palette. The Brisket has such a nice smoked flavor though that I preferred eating it solo and letting it melt in the mouth.  Definitely coming back to try the ribs.

Visited Urban nomads for the first time this week, and had a wonderful experience. It's a new restaurant in the area that combines Asian and American food with great BBQ styles. We got the Fondue Pork Frites appetizer, featured in picture 2, and it was phenomenal! I then had their boulgogi while my partner had the BBQ pork sandwich, along with their homemade BBQ sauce , which were also both fantastic. The only critique I could say is that the menus didn't have what everything came with the meal listed, so we were pleasantly surprised when the sandwich came with fries and the beef came with rice and cabbage.  The staff are also super nice and very invested in their business, while doing a great job and providing fantastic food. If you get a chance, definitely recommend giving it a try!! They'll have their liquor license soon and will be going in full swing, and I know I'll be back to try it again Soon.
My wife and I had lovely anniversary dinner here and it was amazing. The service, wine, food, ambiance, everything was great. I would definitely go back

Amazing burger! Cooked to perfection. Great service as well!
Get the skewers, chicken or beef, either way they're amazing. So tender and juicy, and a great char without being overcooked! Also the lunch special burger can't be beat.
Absolutely a place worth visiting, the food is awesome and well prepared, the cost is affordable and it is constantly neat here. Great work.

Ordered the Po’Boy and husband ordered the burger and both were great as well as the fries! Service was very fast and sincere. I was surprised there weren’t more customers when we were there. I would definitely go back next time I’m in Lincoln Park!
Good food
This spot is one of my favorites! Fair rates, considerable dishes and the staff are constantly very friendly.

First time ordered the smoky bird!! 1/2 chicken with rice and broccoli. It was delicious,  they had a side of their sauce, which I appreciate to add as you choose. The smoked chicken was perfect,  as was the rice and broccoli. I definitely will order again from this gem in Lakeview!
You can't go wrong with meat skewers!  We stumbled on this while walking north and went in.  Glad we did. Food was delicious and the staff was great
The Mongolian Meatlover’s Platter we ordered was enough to feed two people. Chicken skewers were the best! The rest was good as well.
So good amazing burger
Very good and also very good lunch deals! Fresh and made to order. Would be back!
We enjoyed a tasty family meal here. The adults had great chicken skewers and pulled pork bbq and the kids liked the basics from the kids menu.
Their smoked sandwiches were really good. I will definitely recommend this place to everyone I know. Keep up the good work.

Not sure why this spot hasn’t gained more attention, it’s delicious! Vibe is a little strange, it’s caught between fast casual and a sit down restaurant. Not many people dine in. Food is incredible though and prices are fair for bbq in the area. My suggestion to get ppl in the door would be to change up the branding and menu design so it reads more as a fresh Mongolian bbq eatery.

Owner actually served us. She was awesome and you can tell she cares a lot about the place and how her clients feel. Great food. Great portions. Its like fusion American and Mongolian, but appealing to the tastes of both. Absolutely try it.
First decent meal I had in America. Meal was perfect, hostess was very hospitable and quick with the refills of our water and food was very good. Thank you for the meal!

Blink and you'll miss it, but this place is serving some of the BEST BBQ.  Southern/ Texas style BBQ fused with bit of Mongoian/ Asian influence, they are putting out some EXCELLENT food at an affordable price point. The brisket is excellent

I have been here for few times, and as always excellent food +service! I was so hungry after work out wanted to eat healthy, since usually I come with a company for burgers and man the dessert. But they make excellent salad with the skewers ( guessing upon request) No added flavors and sauces, loved it!

I'm always excited when I see new restaurants open up in my neighborhood, and I was extremely thrilled when I realized what kind of cuisine Urban Nomads would be featuring within their walls. For a few weeks, my boyfriend and I have casually spoken about visiting this restaurant "very soon," And yesterday we were finally able to take some time Out of our busy schedules to walk over and sit down to experience it. I am extremely glad that we finally did, and after just one visit, we can gladly say that we will be back many, many times again!  We weren't sure if this place was BYOB or not, because no one had added it to Yelp yet, and we didn't see any alcohol on the menu online, but please know that if they weren't before, they are definitely BYOB now! We saw this displayed on their front window, and on a chalkboard outside while we were approaching. We live very close by so we figured we would just have a drink at home afterward since we forgot to bring alcohol, but if you are really looking to enjoy your dinner with a few sips of alcohol, there is a liquor store a few doors down where you can buy some. There's no corkage fee and no additional costs for bringing in your own drinks, and they have glasses and cups for whatever you bring in.  We stopped in yesterday, which was a Saturday around 6 o'clock or 6:30, and we were surprised because it wasn't very busy. We were cheerfully greeted by a woman behind the counter and were told that we could select where we wanted to sit. We chose a booth right by the front window, but I don't think there's a bad seat in the house. There was cheerful pop music playing over the speakers with some music videos on TVs behind the counter, and gorgeous wood lined the entire walls. The booth was comfortable and everything looked very clean.  We had perused the menu online before stopping in, so we both pretty much knew what we wanted: we ordered a hummus platter to start, and my boyfriend was very excited about the photo of the po'boy he saw online, so he got that. I went with a half rack of ribs which came with broccoli and rice, and was surprisingly only $15. I feel like that's a pretty low price for ribs!  Our food came out very quickly, and we were in awe of every last bit. The hummus plate featured cucumbers, celery, carrots and warm pita, and the hummus had spices that gave it extra flavor. My ribs fell right off the bone and are a STEAL at $15. I can't believe they're so inexpensive for how delicious, and they're smoked overnight! Amazing. We truly enjoyed Urban Nomads and will be bringing our friends and family when they want to go to dinner.  It's a no-brainer: be one of the first to experience Urban Nomads! You won't regret it.

Last couple months I was in Chicago. I have difficult time to find the restaurant that have Mongolian food. So we just came to this restaurant. It is so good. The food so yummy and staff very nice. Will coming back again next trip.
The meat platter was very tasty and the broccoli was insanely good...
Great Mongolian BBQ and friendly owner!
Skewers was good.
Excellent food and service!!
I love it. it’s so delicious

Just checked this place out. I find the grill work to be outstanding compared to others in the vicinity as they also have very delectable cheeseburgers, also best choice of Mongolian barbecue in the city! Highly recommend this new restaurant.
Food is great here, juicy and delicious!
Great food , great staff . Loved it. Best food we had in Chicago

The food was delicious. I got a cheeseburger, ordered medium but got closer to rare. It was so good I ate every bit of it though. The homemade chips were thick and crispy. My only complaint was that they had a kid's menu and soup on the menu but when we tried to order those things we were told that they weren't serving those items. Unfortunately my 7 year old didn't want anything else on the menu and the rest of us had already ordered. We ended up just getting her side dishes.

This is my first time here and I have to say I'm impressed! The decor is subtle and totally upholds the name of the restaurant.  I ordered a classic cheeseburger and it was delicious, very flavorful and juicy.  The fries are also tasty and I'm very picky about French fries but they were crispy and well seasoned.  The hostess and chef were super nice and personable.  I really enjoyed this quaint establishment.  I also got green tea icecream 😋

My brother recommended a new restaurant to my husband and I for us to all go try together after he said he had a burger there that he wanted to go back for ever since. Our server was incredibly kind and Chef Alexander came out to talk with us and tell us about some of the dishes he was serving after recognizing my brother from the first time he came in. My favorite offerings of the evening were the chicken wings with a berry hot sauce and the flour-less chocolate cake.  Alexander told us he grows the berries for the sauce in his own garden and you can really tell the difference. This is a great community restaurant and I'm sure we'll be back soon. The care and love that goes into this food is truly something special.
Finally had the chance to try out this place, Delicious Food and great service! Must visit , will recommend to my all friends. So good! So tasty!
Food was amazing. So happy that we found this place.
